adjectives.description: selflike (comparative more selflike, superlative most selflike)

entries.meaning: Of or pertaining to self or one's self; personal; individual; own.
examples: But this is precisely what Shpet does: he projects onto the "word-concept" selflike qualities that are by no means necessarily foreseen in Husserl, suggesting at once that our selves are structured like it and that it is a kind of self [...]
Because the selflike (selbstische) universality, the subjective One (Bins) of the individuality, does not separate itself from the real particularization but is only submerged in it, [...]
